doc.ContractDescription: IGF::OT::IGF MOAKLEY FEDERAL COURTHOUSE, BOSTON, MA THIS MOD PA01 SHALL SERVE TO CORRECT, IN THE DESCRIPTION, THE PUBLIC REALM EVENT FROM E816 TO E822.

NEW DISCOVERIES MADE IN RECENT OBSERVATIONS AT VENUS AND MARS AND NEW LABORATORY DATA ON KEY REACTION RATE COEFFICIENTS NOW ENABLE COMPARATIVE STUDIES OF THE EFFECTS OF METEOROIDS ON MULTIPLE PLANETS. METEOROIDS DEPOSIT EXOTIC SPECIES LIKE MG AND FE INTO AN ATMOSPHERE WHEN THEY ABLATE. THESE SPECIES ARE EASILY IONIZED INTO LONG-LIVED ATOMIC IONS AND THEREFORE MODIFY THE QUIESCENT STRUCTURES OF THE IONOSPHERES OF VENUS, EARTH, AND MARS. METEORIC PLASMA LAYERS HAVE RECENTLY BEEN OBSERVED FOR THE FIRST TIME ON VENUS AND MARS. HERE WE PROPOSE A THREE-PART, THREE-YEAR EFFORT TO STUDY THIS BASIC IONOSPHERIC PHENOMENON ON VENUS AND MARS. OUR EFFORTS WILL COMMENCE WITH A SURVEY OF THE TYPICAL PROPERTIES OF OBSERVED METEORIC LAYERS ON VENUS, ALONG THE LINES OF OUR PAST WORK AT MARS (WITHERS ET AL., 2008A), THAT WILL INCLUDE A SEARCH FOR TRENDS LINKING OBSERVABLE CHARACTERISTICS TO EXTERNAL FACTORS SUCH AS SOLAR ZENITH ANGLE (TASK A: COMPARISON OF BASIC OBSERVED PROPERTIES AT VENUS AND MARS). THE RESULTS OF THIS TASK AND OUR PRIOR MARS WORK WILL SERVE AS THE BENCHMARK FOR SUBSEQUENT NUMERICAL MODELING. NEXT, WE WILL UPDATE AN EXISTING ONE-DIMENSIONAL MODEL FOR THE PRODUCTION, TRANSPORT, AND LOSS OF METEORIC PLASMA ON VENUS AND MARS (TASK B: INITIAL APPLICATION OF MODEL FOR VENUS AND MARS). ONCE THE MODEL IS READY, WE WILL COMPARE PREDICTED LAYERS TO THOSE OBSERVED, SIMULATE VARIATIONS WITH SOLAR ZENITH ANGLE, AND CALCULATE THE LIFETIME OF METEORIC PLASMA. FINALLY, WE WILL EXPLORE HOW METEORIC LAYER PROPERTIES VARY DUE TO PLAUSIBLE VARIATIONS IN EXPECTED METEOROID INFLUX PROPERTIES (TASK C: EFFECTS OF VARIATIONS IN METEOROID INFLUX AT VENUS AND MARS). THE ANALYSIS OF METEORIC LAYER OBSERVATIONS IS A POTENTIAL TOOL FOR CONSTRAINING THE METEOROID FLUX AT THE ORBITS OF VENUS AND MARS, WHICH CAN PROVIDE BETTER UNDERSTANDING OF THE SOLAR SYSTEM DUST ENVIRONMENT AND ITS CONNECTIONS TO THE POPULATION AND DYNAMICAL EVOLUTION OF SMALL BODIES.

doc.ContractDescription: STUDIES OF MASSIVE GALAXY CLUSTERS AND GROUPS AT REDSHIFTS BELOW 1 TYPICALLY FIND ENVIRONMENTS WITH LITTLE-TO-NO STAR FORMATION ACTIVITY, IN SHARP CONTRAST WITH THE FIELD. OVER-DENSE REGIONS ARE DOMINATED BY PASSIVELY-EVOLVING SPHEROIDAL (S0) AND ELLIPTICAL GALAXIES, WHEREAS GALAXIES IN THE FIELD TEND TO HAVE SPIRAL MORPHOLOGIES, YOUNGER STELLAR POPULATIONS, AND SYSTEMATICALLY HIGHER STAR FORMATION RATES. STUDIES OF THE GALAXY POPULATIONS OF CLUSTERS AND MASSIVE GALAXY GROUPS HAVE FOUND THAT THE INCREASE IN THE FRACTION OF SPIRALS AT HIGHER REDSHIFTS CORRESPONDS TO A DECLINE IN THE FRACTION OF S0 GALAXIES, WHICH STRONGLY SUGGESTS THAT FIELD SPIRALS ARE TRANSFORMED INTO S0 GALAXIES AT SOME POINT IN THEIR TRANSITION BETWEEN FIELD AND CLUSTER REGIONS. THIS TRANSFORMATION NECESSARILY INVOLVES AN INCREASE IN THE STELLAR CONTENT OF THE BULGE RELATIVE TO THE DISK, AND THEN A REMOVAL OF DISK GAS ACCOMPANIED BY EITHER A RAPID OR GRADUAL DECLINE IN STAR FORMATION TO EVENTUALLY PRODUCE A RED, SPHEROIDAL, PASSIVELY-EVOLVING S0 GALAXY. DEEP AND WIDE AREA COSMOLOGICAL SURVEYS SUCH AS THE GOODS AND COSMOS HAVE SHOWN THAT BOTH ENVIRONMENT AND STELLAR MASS PLAY A DISTINCT ROLE IN THE OVERALL GALAXY EVOLUTION OVER A WIDE REDSHIFT RANGE (TO Z~3). THE DENSITY-MORPHOLOGY RELATION AND THE BLUE-FRACTION, FIRST NOTED IN THE TARGETED STUDIES OF CLUSTERS AND GROUPS, ALSO APPEARS TO BE AN EXTENSION OF THE EVOLUTIONARY TRENDS SEEN IN THE FIELD SAMPLE. HOWEVER, THE TRENDS SEEN IN THESE LARGE COSMOLOGICAL SURVEYS SHOULD BE TAKEN WITH A CAUTION SINCE THEY ARE BROAD STATISTICAL TRENDS OF PRIMARILY MASSIVE GALAXIES WITH RELATIVELY POOR SENSITIVITY ON STAR FORMATION RATE (SFR), ASSOCIATED WITH A RELATIVELY NARROW RANGE OF SPARSELY SAMPLED GALAXY DENSITY. THIS CAN LEAD TO POTENTIALLY SERIOUS SHORTCOMINGS WHEN STUDYING THE ROLE OF ENVIRONMENT BECAUSE MANY OF THE PHYSICAL MECHANISMS INVOLVED MAY PREFERENTIALLY IMPACT THE LOWER MASS GALAXIES. THE DOMINANT PHYSICAL MECHANISM(S) RESPONSIBLE FOR THIS TRANSFORMATION ARE STILL BEING DEBATED, BUT THE OVERWHELMING EVIDENCE HAS SHOWN THAT SPIRALS ARE READILY ALTERED IN GROUPS OR CLUSTER OUTSKIRTS PRIOR TO FALLING INTO A GALAXY CLUSTER (PRE-PROCESSING). THIS IMPLIES THAT THE BEST APPROACH TO CATCH GALAXY TRANSFORMATION IN THE ACT IS TO EXAMINE GALAXIES IN LOWER DENSITY ENVIRONMENTS. A COMPLETE ACCOUNTING OF STAR-FORMATION ACTIVITY FOR GALAXIES OVER A WIDE RANGE MASSES AND ENVIRONMENTS IS NEEDED TO ASSESS WHICH OF MANY POSSIBLE MECHANISMS IS THE DOMINANT CAUSE OF GALAXY TRANSFORMATION IN OVER-DENSE REGIONS. THE MAIN GOAL OF THIS PROPOSED STUDY IS TO EXAMINE THE SF AND QUENCHING ACTIVITIES ASSOCIATED WITH GALAXIES USING THE HIGH SPATIAL RESOLUTION OF THE TARGETED STUDIES OF INDIVIDUAL CLUSTERS, BUT COVERING MUCH LARGER AREAS AND DENSITY RANGES (FROM VOIDS TO CLUSTER CORES) WITH THE SAMPLE STATISTICS APPROACHING THOSE OF THE COSMOLOGICAL SURVEYS SUCH AS COSMOS, USING EXQUISITE STELLAR MASS AND SFR (BOTH UV AND IR) SENSITIVITY. TO ACHIEVE THIS, WE PROPOSE A MULTI-WAVELENGTH STUDY (WITH A SPECIFIC EMPHASIS ON GALEX AND WISE) OF THE TWO MOST PROMINENT LARGE SCALE STRUCTURES IN THE LOCAL UNIVERSE: THE COMA AND PERSEUS-PISCES SUPERCLUSTERS. THE TOTAL SAMPLE AREA COVERS ~3000 SQ. DEGREE AND CONTAINS ABOUT 7000 SPECTROSCOPICALLY IDENTIFIED GALAXIES (FROM SDSS AND ARCHIVAL SPECTRA). IN ADDITION, WE WILL EVALUATE THE IMPACTS OF THE HIGH MASS AND SFR CUT EMPLOYED BY DEEP COSMOLOGICAL SURVEYS BY PARING DOWN OUR SAMPLE IN STELLAR MASS AND SFR (AND RESULTING COARSE GALAXY DENSITY ESTIMATES) AND EXAMINE WHETHER ANY IMPORTANT INSIGHTS ARE MISSED AS A RESULT.

doc.ContractDescription: SUPERNOVAE INJECT METALS AT HIGH VELOCITIES INTO THE INTERSTELLAR MEDIUM (ISM), LEADING TO SHOCKS, PLASMA HEATING, AND DUST DESTRUCTION AND CREATION IN ADDITION TO HOST OF OTHER PROCESSES. SUPERNOVA REMNANTS (SNR) THEMSELVES ARE GENERALLY CATEGORIZED AS SHELL-TYPE, CENTER-FILLED, OR ``MIXED MORPHOLOGY.'' THESE CATEGORIES, WHICH ENCAPSULATE BOTH THE STRUCTURE AND EVOLUTION OF THE REMNANT, SEEM TO DEPEND CRITICALLY ON THE PRECURSOR STAR AND THE SURROUNDING ISM. MIXED MORPHOLOGY REMNANTS, IN PARTICULAR, SHOW A RADIO SHELL WITH A CENTRAL REGION THAT EMITS PRIMARILY THERMAL X-RAYS. OBSERVATIONS SHOW THAT THESE SNR ARE TYPICALLY FOUND NEAR OR IN MOLECULAR CLOUDS AND, SINCE THEY USUALLY CONTAIN COMPACT OBJECTS, ARISE FROM HIGH-MASS PRECURSORS. HOWEVER, OUR THEORETICAL UNDERSTANDING OF THESE REMNANTS LAGS FAR BEHIND OUR OBSERVATIONAL DATA. THERE ARE AT LEAST FOUR DISTINCT MODELS FOR THEIR APPEARANCE, USUALLY EXPLAINING OBSERVATIONS FROM ONE OR AT MOST A FEW OF THE REMNANTS, BUT THERE IS NO GENERAL SOLUTION. HOWEVER, THERE HAS BEEN A RECENT BREAKTHROUGH IN MIXED MORPHOLOGY REMNANTS. SUZAKU OBSERVATIONS OF THREE REMNANTS SHOW THAT A SIGNIFICANT FRACTION OF THE THERMAL X-RAYS ARE FROM A NON-EQUILIBRIUM RECOMBINING PLASMA, A SURPRISING RESULT SINCE SNR ARE EXPECTED TO GENERATE IONIZING, NOT RECOMBINING, PLASMAS. THIS NEW DISCOVERY SHOULD SEVERELY CONSTRAINS THEORETICAL PREDICTIONS. WE PROPOSE A COMBINED SEMI-ANALYTIC AND COMPUTATIONAL APPROACH TO UNDERSTANDING HOW THESE REMNANTS DEVELOP AND EVOLVE. A NUMBER OF OBSERVATIONAL STUDIES HAVE ALREADY CATALOGED THE EMISSION CHARACTERISTICS AND SIZES OF THESE REMNANTS. OUR STUDY WILL THEREFORE BEGIN WITH AN EXPLORATION OF SIMPLE 1-D SPHERICALLY SYMMETRIC HYDRODYNAMIC PLASMA MODELS THAT CAN GENERATE THE OBSERVED EMISSION IN X-RAY AND OTHER BANDPASSES AS WELL AS THE APPROXIMATE SIZE OF A RANGE OF MIXED MORPHOLOGY REMNANTS. WE WILL EXPAND THESE STUDIES USING BOTH 2-D AND 3-D MAGNETOHYDRODYNAMIC EXPLOSION MODELS COMBINED WITH A NON-EQUILIBRIUM PLASMA CODE TO CALCULATE THE THERMAL X-RAY EMISSION. THESE MODELS WILL BE ABLE TO CAPTURE THE TURBULENCE AND EJECTA MIXING THAT MUST HAPPEN IN THESE REMNANTS THAT CANNOT BE SIMULATED IN 1-D. WE WILL THEN DETERMINE THE EMISSION AS A FUNCTION OF POSITION IN VARIOUS BANDPASSES FOR OUR MODELS WITH A RANGE OF INITIAL CONDITIONS. THIS WILL ALLOW US TO DETERMINING WHICH OBSERVABLES ARE THE KEY TO UNDERSTANDING THE ORIGIN AND EVOLUTION OF MIXED MORPHOLOGY REMNANTS, AND THEIR OVERALL IMPACT ON THE ISM AND THE GALAXY. THIS WORK WILL ADDRESS NASA'S STRATEGIC SUBGOAL 3D, TO DISCOVER THE ORIGIN, STRUCTURE, EVOLUTION, AND DESTINY OF THE UNIVERSE, AND SEARCH FOR EARTH-LIKE PLANETS.

doc.ContractDescription: THE OBJECTIVE OF THE PROPOSED STUDY IS TO CHARACTERIZE THE STRUCTURE AND DYNAMICS OF THE HELIOSHEATH AND THE HELIOPAUSE (HP) WITH THE INCLUSION OF PICK-UP IONS (PUIS) AND TIME-DEPENDENT SOLAR WIND. VOYAGER HAS MADE IN SITU MEASUREMENTS OF THE HELIOSPHERE ALONG THEIR TWO TRAJECTORIES AND IBEX HAS PROVIDED A GLOBAL VIEW OF THE HELIOSPHERE USING ENERGETIC NEUTRAL ATOMS (ENAS). THE HELIOSHEATH SEEM TO BE MORE MYSTERIOUS THAT WE PREVIOUSLY THOUGHT. VOYAGER 1 (V1) AND 2 ARE PROVIDING VERY DISTINCT FLOWS THAT NEITHER OF THE CURRENT MODELS CAN EXPLAIN. V1 FLOW IN PARTICULAR DROPPED TO ZERO VALUES OVER A RANGE OF 10AU AT LEAST BEFORE THE HP. THE ENERGETIC ELECTRONS ON V2 HAVE VARIATIONS OF ORDERS OF MAGNITUDE WHILE ON V1 THEY ARE CONSTANT. OTHER ENERGETIC PARTICLES HAVE SIMILAR DISTINCT BEHAVIOR ON V1 AND 2 RANGING FROM KEV ENERGIES TO THE GALACTIC COSMIC RAYS. THESE OBSERVATIONS INDICATE THAT NEW IDEAS HAVE TO BE BROUGHT UP TO THE TABLE TO BE INCORPORATED IN GLOBAL MHD MODELS. THE DISTRIBUTED ENA MAPS (THE MAPS WHERE THE RIBBON IS REMOVED) PROVIDED BY IBEX REVEAL THE INTEGRATED GLOBAL BEHAVIOR OF THE HELIOSHEATH. IBEX ENA MAPS SHOW A LATITUDINAL DEPENDENCE OF THE SPECTRA AS WELL AS TIME DEPENDENCE. WITH THE APPROACH OF VOYAGER SPACECRAFTS TO THE HP IT BECOME IMPORTANT TO PREDICT THE NATURE OF THE HP. WITH THE INCREASE OF ACTIVITY FROM THE SUN, AFTER THE RECENT EXTENDED SOLAR MINIMA, THE INCLUSION OF TIME-DEPENDENT EFFECTS BECOMES ESPECIALLY IMPORTANT IN ORDER TO CHARACTERIZE THE HELIOSHEATH. WE PROPOSE TO USE OUR RECENT EXTENSION OF OUR MODEL THAT INCLUDES THE PUIS AS A SEPARATE FLUID AND INVESTIGATE SEVERAL QUESTIONS RELATED TO THE SPATIAL AND TEMPORAL NATURE OF THE HELIOSHEATH: HOW ARE THE GLOBAL FLOWS AND MAGNETIC FIELDS ARE AFFECTED IN A HELIOSHEATH DOMINATED BY THE THERMAL PRESSURE FROM PUIS HOW DOES RECONNECTION IN THE SECTOR REGION AFFECTS THE FLOWS IN THE HELIOSHEATH CAN ONE MODEL REPRODUCE V1 AND 2 OBSERVATIONS OF FLOWS AND MAGNETIC FIELDS IS THERE A HELIOPAUSE TRANSITION LAYER HOW THICK IS IT WHAT IS ITS STRUCTURE THROUGH THE GLOBAL ENA MAPS CAN WE UNRAVEL THE GLOBAL STRUCTURE OF FLOWS IN THE HELIOSHEATH WHAT ARE THE GLOBAL SIGNS THAT TELL US THAT THE CROSSING OF THE HP IS IMMINENT (BOTH AT V1 AND V2 HOW THE SOLAR CYCLE VARIATIONS OF SOLAR WIND IN A HELIOSHEATH THERMALLY DOMINATED BY PUI AFFECT THE FLOWS AND FIELDS CAN WE PREDICT TEMPORAL VARIATIONS IN THE GLOBAL ENA MAPS OUR TEAM HAS THE NECESSARY EXPERTISE IN THEORY AND MODELING. THE PI AND CO-IS PARTICIPATE ACTIVELY IN THE VOYAGER AND IBEX SCIENCE TEAM MEETINGS AND ARE MEMBERS OF BOTH MISSION TEAMS. WE WILL CLOSELY COMPARE WITH AND PREDICT THE OBSERVATIONS FROM V1 AND 2 THROUGH ADVICE AND GUIDANCE FROM THE VOYAGER TEAM. WE WILL COLLABORATE WITH THE OTHER IBEX TEAM MEMBERS WHEN COMPARING THE GLOBAL ENA MAPS TO MODELS. doc.ContractDescription: THEORETICAL STUDIES OF WEAK GRAVITATIONAL LENSING. OBSERVATIONS OF WEAK GRAVITATIONAL LENSING ALLOW THE AMOUNT AND DISTRIBUTION OF DARK MATTER IN THE UNIVERSE TO BE MAPPED WITH GREAT ACCURACY. IN ADDITION, OBSERVATIONS OF WEAK LENSING CAN BE USED TO PLACE STRONG CONSTRAINTS ON THE VALUES OF THE FUNDAMENTAL COSMOLOGICAL PARAMETERS, AS WELL AS ON THE RATE AT WHICH DENSITY FLUCTUATIONS GREW IN THE UNIVERSE. THE PROPER INTERPRETATION OF THESE WEAK LENSING OBSERVATIONS REQUIRES THE USE OF SIMULATIONS WHEN DISTANT GALAXIES IN THE UNIVERSE HAVE BEEN LENSED AT A COMPARABLE LEVEL BY TWO OR MORE FOREGROUND LENSES. THIS IS A COMMON OCCURRENCE WHEN THE LENSING IMPACT PARAMETER IS RELATIVELY SMALL AND THE IMAGING DATA ARE VERY DEEP. THE PROPOSED WORK WILL DEVELOP THE THEORETICAL GROUNDWORK THAT WILL BE NECESSARY FOR INTERPRETING FUTURE OBSERVATIONS OF WEAK LENSING. THESE FUTURE OBSERVATIONAL STUDIES WILL ULTIMATELY BE FACILITATED BY THE WIDE FIELD INFRARED TELESCOPE (WFIRST), THE TOP-RANKED LARGE SPACE MISSION FROM ASTRO2010. THE PROPOSED WORK CONSISTS OF THREE STUDIES AND WILL INCLUDE RAY TRACING SIMULATIONS OF COSMOLOGICAL WEAK LENSING EFFECTS, AS WELL AS THE EXPANSION OF EXISTING THEORY FOR WEAK LENSING DUE TO THE DARK MATTER HALOS OF GALAXIES. THE FIRST STUDY WILL FOCUS ON THE WEAK LENSING EFFECT KNOWN AS COSMIC MAGNIFICATION. COSMIC MAGNIFICATION IS BEING ACTIVELY INVESTIGATED BY THE WEAK LENSING COMMUNITY AS A POWERFUL COMPLEMENT TO THE WEAK LENSING EFFECT KNOWN AS COSMIC SHEAR. CURRENTLY, THE THEORY OF COSMIC MAGNIFICATION IS NOT WELL-ESTABLISHED ON SCALES LESS THAN 1 MPC, AND THESE ARE THE SCALES THAT WILL BE INVESTIGATED. THE SECOND AND THIRD STUDIES WILL CENTER ON THE WEAK LENSING PHENOMENON KNOWN AS GALAXY-GALAXY LENSING. THE SECOND STUDY WILL DETERMINE THE CHARACTERISTIC SIGNATURES OF ANISOTROPIC GALAXY-GALAXY LENSING, AN EFFECT THAT OCCURS WHEN THE DARK MATTER HALOS OF GALAXIES ARE NON-SPHERICAL. NON-SPHERICAL DARK MATTER HALOS ARE A PREDICTION OF THE COLD DARK MATTER (CDM) MODEL FOR STRUCTURE FORMATION. THE THIRD STUDY WILL DETERMINE WHETHER THE POPULAR THEORETICAL FRAMEWORK KNOWN AS THE HALO MODEL CAN BE USED TO PLACE STRONG CONSTRAINTS ON THE DARK MATTER DISTRIBUTION SURROUNDING WEAK GALAXY LENSES IN THE LIMIT OF VERY DEEP DATA, FOR WHICH MULTIPLE WEAK LENSING EVENTS ARE COMMON. THE PRIMARY OBJECTIVES OF THE PROPOSED INVESTIGATION ARE TO: [1] DETERMINE THE CONTRIBUTION OF GALAXIES, GALAXY GROUPS, AND GALAXY CLUSTERS TO THE COSMIC MAGNIFICATION SIGNAL, [2] QUANTIFY THE EFFECTS OF ERRORS IN THE SEPARATION OF FOREGROUND AND BACKGROUND GALAXIES ON THE COSMIC MAGNIFICATION SIGNAL, [3] DEVELOP THE WEAK LENSING THEORY OF SMOOTHLY-TRUNCATED, NON-SPHERICAL CDM HALOS, [4] DETERMINE THE DEGREE TO WHICH THE GALAXY-GALAXY LENSING SIGNAL IN OUR UNIVERSE SHOULD BE ANISOTROPIC, [5]DEVELOP A METHODOLOGY BY WHICH OBSERVATIONS OF ANISOTROPIC GALAXY-GALAXY LENSING MAY BE REDUCED TO A SINGLE-LENS PROBLEM (INCLUDING AN ASSESSMENT OF THE DEGREE TO WHICH RESULTS FROM SUCH AN INVESTIGATION WOULD BIAS CONCLUSIONS ABOUT THE OVERALL SHAPE DISTRIBUTION OF DARK MATTER HALOS), AND [6] QUANTIFY THE DIFFERENCES BETWEEN THE CIRCULARLY-AVERAGED GALAXY-GALAXY LENSING SIGNAL THAT RESULTS FROM A FULL MULTIPLE-DEFLECTION CALCULATION, VERSUS THE SIGNAL THAT RESULTS FROM AN APPLICATION OF THE HALO MODEL. THROUGHOUT, THE THEORETICAL CALCULATIONS WILL BE CONDUCTED IN THE FRAMEWORK OF A LAMBDA-CDM UNIVERSE SINCE THIS HAS PROVEN TO BE THE MOST SUCCESSFUL MODEL FOR REPRODUCING THE OBSERVED LARGE-SCALE STRUCTURE OF THE UNIVERSE. RESULTS OF THIS WORK WILL ALLOW STRONG TESTS OF LAMBDA-CDM TO BE PERFORMED ON SCALES RANGING FROM 20 KPC/H TO 1 MPC/H USING FUTURE DEEP IMAGING DATA, SUCH AS THAT WHICH WILL BE OBTAINED BY WFIRST.

doc.ContractDescription: QUASARS AND AGNS SHOW CHARACTERISTIC HOT DUST EMISSION NOT SEEN IN OTHER OBJECTS. THIS IS DUE TO AN OBSCURING "TORUS" IN THE INNER REGIONS OF THE QUASAR. UNDERSTANDING OF THIS "TORUS" HAS PROGRESSED SLOWLY IN THE PAST 2+ DECADES. BASED ON OUR WISEBASED PILOT PROJECT WE FIND A WIDE RANGE OF IR (DUST) TO OPTICAL (ACCRETION DISK) EMISSION RATIOS IN QUASAR SPECTRAL ENERGY DISTRIBUTIONS (SEDS). THIS IMPLIES ORDER OF MAGNITUDE DIFFERENCES IN THE COVERING FACTOR OF THE OBSCURING "TORUS" FROM OBJECT TO OBJECT. MOREOVER THE NEAR-IR (HOT DUST) TO MID-IR (WARM DUST) RATIO VARIES BY A SIMILAR FACTOR, SO THE STRUCTURE WITHIN THE "TORUS" ALSO VARIES GREATLY FROM OBJECT TO OBJECT. THE RESULTS WILL INFORM US NOT ONLY ABOUT THE INNER STRUCTURE OF QUASARS, BUT ALSO OF THE MECHANISM THAT BRINGS MATTER INTO BOUND ORBIT AROUND THE CENTRAL SUPERMASSIVE BLACK HOLE (SMBH). METHODS: WE PROPOSE TO ANALYZE THE WISE DATA FOR 24,257 SDSS BROAD EMISSION LINE, TYPE 1, QUASARS THAT ALSO LIE IN THE NEAR-IR UKIDSS SURVEY TO PRODUCE OPTICAL-MID-IR SEDS. THE PROPERTIES OF THE DUST-EMITTING REGION WILL BE OUR PRIMARY FOCUS. PREVIOUS SAMPLES HAVE BEEN LIMITED TO A FEW HUNDRED QUASAR SEDS. WITH THIS LARGE SAMPLE WE CAN SEARCH FOR SYSTEMATIC SED CHANGES WITH REDSHIFT, LUMINOSITY AND WITH PHYSICAL PARAMETERS DERIVED FROM THE SDSS SPECTRA: BLACK HOLE MASS AND EDDINGTON RATIO. WE WILL USE THE 'MIXING DIAGRAM' METHOD DEVELOPED FOR COSMOS, PLUS THEORY BASED CLUMPY TORUS AND WARPED DISK MODELS. SIGNIFICANCE: THE GROWTH OF SUPERMASSIVE BLACK HOLES IS A CENTRAL PART OF GALAXY EVOLUTION AND COSMOLOGY, YET IS POORLY UNDERSTOOD. THE "TORUS" IS LIKELY THE RESEVOIR FROM WHICH THE ACCRETION DISK IS FED, BUT HOW IT FORMS IS UNKNOWN. MOREOVER AGN "FEEDBACK" IS THOUGHT TO HAVE A MAJOR EFFECT ON THE EVOLUTION OF GALAXIES, REGULATING STAR FORMATION. HOWEVER, THE INFLUENCE OF THE CENTRAL AGN ON ITS HOST GALAXY IS LIMITED IF THE "TORUS" INTERCEPTS MOST OF AGN CONTINUUM, OR BLOCKS ACCRETION DISK WINDS. OUR PROJECT WILL ADDRESS BOTH ISSUES DIRECTLY.

doc.ContractDescription: THIS PROPOSAL REQUESTS SUPPORT TO PRODUCE, DOCUMENT, AND DISTRIBUTE A POINT SOURCE CATALOG DERIVED FROM THE SPITZER SPACE TELESCOPE MIPSGAL SURVEY OF 24 MICRON EMISSION ALONG THE GALACTIC PLANE AND TO ESTIMATE THE LATENCY OF MASSIVE STAR FORMATION WITHIN MASSIVE CORES OF GIANT MOLECULAR CLOUDS USING THIS SOURCE CATALOG. A MIPSGAL SOURCE CATALOG WILL ADD SIGNIFICANT VALUE TO THIS SPITZER LEGACY PROGRAM AS IT PROVIDES UNIFORM AND RELIABLE SOURCE EXTRACTION AND PHOTOMETRIC ALGORITHMS FOR THE ENTIRE SURVEYED AREA AND ENABLES A DIVERSE RANGE OF SCIENTIFIC INVESTIGATIONS BY THE ASTRONOMICAL COMMUNITY. THE CATALOG WILL BE DELIVERED TO IPAC TO SERVE TO THE COMMUNITY. WE WILL EXPLOIT THE INFORMATION RESIDENT WITHIN THE SOURCE CATALOG TO COMPILE A LIST OF MASSIVE, NEWBORN STARS IN THE EARLIEST PHASES OF PROTOSTELLAR EVOLUTION AND THEIR SPATIAL COINCIDENCE WITH DENSE CLUMPS WITHIN GMCS IDENTIFIED BY THEIR SUBMILLIMETER DUST CONTINUUM EMISSION. FROM THESE STATISTICS, THE LATENCY OF MASSIVE STAR FORMATION WITHIN PROTOCLUSTER CLUMPS CAN BE ESTIMATED. THIS LATENCY TIME IS A CRITICAL INPUT TO THEORETICAL DESCRIPTIONS OF STAR FORMATION AND UNDERSTANDING THE FORMATION OF STELLAR CLUSTERS. BY PROVIDING A CRITICAL PRODUCT FROM DATA COLLECTED BY THE SPITZER SPACE TELESCOPE AND ANALYZING ITS CONTENTS, THIS WORK IS IN ACCORD WITH THE NASA STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES AND ROSES SCIENCE GOALS TO DISCOVER THE WORKINGS OF THE UNIVERSE, ITS ORIGIN AND EVOLUTION.
